1 4. A parent participating in the education savings account program shall use the funds
2 deposited in the eligible student's account for the following qualifying expenses to
3 educate the eligible student;
4 a. Tuition and fees at a participating school;
5 b. Textbooks and supplies as required by a participating school;
6 c. Payment for private tutoring or to another educational service provider;
7 d. Payment for educational therapy or services, including occupational therapy,
8 behavioral therapy, physical therapy, speech-language therapy, and audiology
9 therapy from a licensed or certified practitioner or provider, including a licensed or
10 certified paraprofessional or educational aid;
11 e. Payment for purchase of curriculum;
12 f. Tuition or fees for a nonpublic online learning program;
13 g. Fees for national norm-referenced examinations, advanced placement
14 examinations or similar courses, and any examinations related to college or
15 university admission;
16 h. Computer hardware, software, or other technological device that is used solely
17 for a student's educational needs and approved by the department or a licensed
18 physician, provided hardware purchased with education savings account funds
19 may not be resold within one year of purchase;
20 i. Reasonable fees for transportation paid to a fee - for - service transportation
21 provider for the student to travel to and from an education service provider;
22 j. Tuition and fees at an eligible postsecondary institution;
23 k. A textbook required for college or university courses; and
24 l. Upon graduation, a transfer to a North Dakota education savings plan under
25 section 6 - 09 - 38 .
26 5. The administrator may adjust the qualified expenses identified in subsection 4, i f
27 necessary.
28 6. A participating school, private tutor, eligible postsecondary institution, or other
29 education service provider may not refund, rebate, or share a student's grant with a
30 parent or the student in any manner.
