1 b. The department, or an organization chosen by the department, shall:
2 (1) Ensure compliance with all student privacy laws;
3 (2) Collect all test results;
4 (3) Provide the test results, associated learning gains, and graduation rates to
5 the public on the department's website after the third year of test and
6 graduation-related data collection. The findings must be aggregated by the
7 student's grade level, gender, family income level, number of years of
8 participation in the education savings account program , and race ;
9 (4) Provide rates for high school graduation, college attendance, and college
10 graduation for participating students to the public on the department's
11 website after the third year of test and test-related data collection; and
12 (5) Administer an annual parental satisfaction survey requesting each parent of
13 a student receiving an education savings account program grant indicate
14 the number of years the child has participated in the education savings
15 account program and express the parent's:
16 (a) Satisfaction with the education savings account program ; and
17 (b) Opinions on other topics, items, or issues that may indicate the
18 effectiveness of the education savings account program.
19 4. A participating school or other education service provider is autonomous and not an
20 agent of the state or federal government and:
21 a. The departmen t may not regulate the educational program of a participating
22 school or education service provider that accepts funds from an education
23 savings account, except as provided under this chapter and chapter 15.1 - 23 ;
24 b. The creation of the education savings account program does not expand the
25 regulatory authority of the state, its officers, or a school district to impose an
26 additional regulation of participating schools or education service providers
27 beyond the regulations necessary to enforce the requirements of the education
28 savings account program ; and
29 c. Participating schools and education service providers must have the freedom to
30 provide for the educational needs of the school's students without governmental
31 control.
